name: Colors
comment: Contains functions for converting between different color models and manipulating colors. In addition to that, some known colors can be accessed for fast prototyping.

fromRgba.name: fromRgba
fromRgba.comment: Convert a color with vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.fromRgba.r, vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.fromRgba.g, vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.fromRgba.b and vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.fromRgba.a component between 0 and 255 to a color with values between 0.0 and 1.0 and store it in vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.fromRgba.result.

fromHexString.name: fromHexString
fromHexString.comment: Convert the color as a string in the format '#FF0F00', '#FFFF0F00', '#FF0' or '#FFF0' (with or without a leading '#', case insensitive) to the corresponding color value and store it in vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.fromHexString.result. The first group is treated as the alpha channel if a vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.fromHexString.value with four groups is passed.

toHexString.name: toHexString
toHexString.comment: Convert a vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.toHexString.input color to a hex string without a leading '#'. To include the alpha channel, set vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.toHexString.alpha to true, it is false by default.

alphaBlend.name: alphaBlend
alphaBlend.comment: Blend the vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.alphaBlend.foreground color over vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.alphaBlend.background color and store the color in vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.alphaBlend.result.

toGrayscale.name: toGrayscale
toGrayscale.comment: Convert a vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.toGrayscale.input color to a gray scaled color and store it in vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.toGrayscale.result.

linearToGamma.name: linearToGamma
linearToGamma.comment: Convert vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.linearToGamma.linearColor from linear space into gamma color space and store the result in vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.linearToGamma.gammaColor. It is possible to specify a optional vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.linearToGamma.gamma, the default value is 2.2.

gammaToLinear.name: gammaToLinear
gammaToLinear.comment: Convert vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.gammaToLinear.gammaColor from gamma space into linear color space and store the result in vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.gammaToLinear.linearColor. It is possible to specify a optional vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.gammaToLinear.gamma, the default value is 2.2.

rgbToHsv.name: rgbToHsv
rgbToHsv.comment: Convert vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.rgbToHsv.rgbColor from rgb color model to the hue, saturation, and value (HSV) color model and store it in vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.rgbToHsv.hsvColor.

hsvToRgb.name: hsvToRgb
hsvToRgb.comment: Convert vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.hsvToRgb.hsvColor from hue, saturation, and value (HSV) color model to the RGB color model and store it in vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.hsvToRgb.rgbColor.

rgbToHsl.name: rgbToHsl
rgbToHsl.comment: Convert vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.rgbToHsl.rgbColor from rgb color model to the hue, saturation, and lightness (HSL) color model and store it in vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.rgbToHsl.hslColor.

hslToRgb.name: hslToRgb
hslToRgb.comment: Convert vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.hslToRgb.hslColor from hue, saturation, and lightness (HSL) color model to the RGB color model and store it in vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.hslToRgb.rgbColor.

hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of vector_math/vector_math_64.Colors.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.
